WEBVTT

00:01.039 --> 00:02.602
<i>Previously on</i>
Covert Affairs...

00:02.863 --> 00:04.878
The D.C.I.'s asked me
to start a file on you,

00:07.033 --> 00:09.468
Helen's been our cutout,
passing messages between us.

00:09.502 --> 00:11.422
I pulled her in more fully
into Henry's situation

00:11.471 --> 00:12.754
about a week ago.

00:12.805 --> 00:14.590
Director Campbell,
it's an honor to have you.

00:14.641 --> 00:16.058
I'm actually not a director
anymore.

00:16.091 --> 00:17.092
Is one of you guys Reese?

00:17.093 --> 00:18.227
I'm just next door.

00:18.261 --> 00:19.311
I collect the rent,

00:19.345 --> 00:21.013
fix broken toilets
for the landlords,

00:21.047 --> 00:22.014
so he gives me a break.

00:22.048 --> 00:23.315
I'm Sana.

00:23.349 --> 00:24.650
I lost my son, Jai.

00:24.684 --> 00:26.568
Jai was my friend.
I lost him too.

00:26.603 --> 00:29.571
And I think you are smart enough
to help me take Henry down.

00:29.606 --> 00:30.722
Ah, Andrew Goodman.

00:30.740 --> 00:33.391
Bienvenue.
Welcome.

00:34.577 --> 00:36.561
Henry ordered that helicopter
shot down,

00:36.579 --> 00:38.299
and you were the one
that fired the missile.

00:38.331 --> 00:39.665
That's not even a question.

00:40.867 --> 00:42.668
What are you planning on doing
to David Dupres?

00:42.702 --> 00:43.869
Tell her.

00:43.903 --> 00:45.087
Tell her what he's gonna do
to David!

00:45.121 --> 00:46.588
Sana!

00:47.957 --> 00:48.924
Oh!

01:25.745 --> 01:28.714
Why are we stopping here?

01:28.748 --> 01:30.215
I could use a drink.

01:30.249 --> 01:31.917
You?

01:54.440 --> 01:55.741
Can I have a shot of Patron?

01:55.775 --> 01:56.808
What do you want?

01:56.826 --> 01:58.360
Nothing.
I don't want a drink.

01:58.411 --> 02:00.162
Make it two, and can you
charge it to the room?

02:00.196 --> 02:02.197
It's under the name Goodman.

02:03.700 --> 02:05.334
You want to know
what we're doing here?

02:07.704 --> 02:09.503
Henry's been texting Andrew
every half hour

02:09.538 --> 02:11.089
asking for a progress report.

02:11.124 --> 02:12.207
So?

02:12.258 --> 02:13.709
So this
is Andrew Goodman's hotel.

02:13.760 --> 02:15.043
It's the best place
to figure out

02:15.094 --> 02:17.713
how to answer those texts.

02:17.764 --> 02:20.215
What about the dead body
we left in your apartment?

02:20.266 --> 02:22.551
Somebody will have heard
the gunshots.

02:22.602 --> 02:23.769
They're going to find the body.

02:23.803 --> 02:24.936
It's only a matter of when.

02:24.971 --> 02:26.691
That means the police
are gonna be after us,

02:26.723 --> 02:28.603
if they're not already,
as soon as they I.D. it.

02:33.563 --> 02:36.031
It's hard to I.D. a body
with no I.D.

02:36.065 --> 02:38.033
I doubt his name
was even Goodman.

02:38.067 --> 02:39.868
He's a professional ghost.

02:39.902 --> 02:42.204
I'm counting on the fact
that he was good at his job.

02:42.238 --> 02:44.373
Andrew Goodman
will be a John Doe

02:44.407 --> 02:47.459
at least for a little while.

02:47.493 --> 02:49.044
Hopefully, that'll give us
enough time.

02:49.078 --> 02:50.195
Enough time for what?

02:50.213 --> 02:53.665
Counterstrike.

02:53.699 --> 02:55.667
Henry doesn't know
his guy is dead,

02:55.701 --> 02:57.836
so maybe for
the first time ever,

02:57.870 --> 03:00.205
I know something he doesn't.

03:02.708 --> 03:04.342
Drink up.

03:04.377 --> 03:07.062
We're gonna go see what
Andrew Goodman left behind.

03:07.096 --> 03:09.097
Room 425.

03:34.240 --> 03:36.625
You really have no idea
what you're doing, do you?

03:40.913 --> 03:42.881
You stormed
into my interrogation

03:42.915 --> 03:44.549
because you were so desperate
to find out

03:44.583 --> 03:47.219
what Andrew was planning
for David.

03:47.253 --> 03:49.054
Well, Andrew is dead.

03:49.088 --> 03:51.223
The answers are here.

03:51.257 --> 03:52.924
They have to be.

04:23.389 --> 04:24.840
Turn on the TV loud.

04:24.891 --> 04:26.558
Where are you going?

04:37.770 --> 04:39.404
Louder.

04:39.438 --> 04:40.972
Louder.

04:57.656 --> 04:59.207
Turn it off.

05:23.199 --> 05:24.950
Bingo.

05:39.549 --> 05:40.999
I need to decrypt
this password

05:41.033 --> 05:42.667
and find a safe place
to read the drive,

05:42.701 --> 05:44.002
and that's gonna take time--

05:44.036 --> 05:45.503
time that you don't have
right now.

05:45.537 --> 05:47.172
'Cause David's wondering
where I am.

05:47.206 --> 05:48.673
Go home and put him at ease.

05:48.707 --> 05:49.874
Lie to him?

05:49.892 --> 05:52.210
Go through the story again.

05:52.228 --> 05:53.378
I need to hear you say it.

05:53.396 --> 05:55.380
I have lied before.

05:55.398 --> 05:56.714
Say it again.

05:56.732 --> 05:58.716
Go.

05:58.734 --> 06:00.551
When you followed Andrew
out of the meeting,

06:00.570 --> 06:02.220
you were distraught
you'd blown the deal.

06:02.238 --> 06:03.388
We grabbed a drink at a hotel.

06:03.406 --> 06:05.390
I calmed you down,
which took longer

06:05.408 --> 06:06.858
than either of us expected.

06:06.892 --> 06:10.362
You'll be back into work
in the morning, pride bruised,

06:10.396 --> 06:12.030
ready to make it up to David.

06:12.064 --> 06:14.699
Good.

06:14.733 --> 06:16.234
Go home
and try to get some sleep.

06:16.252 --> 06:18.736
Sleep isn't on the cards.

06:18.754 --> 06:21.873
We tortured a man.

06:21.907 --> 06:23.208
You shot him.

06:23.242 --> 06:24.575
He's dead.

06:24.594 --> 06:26.344
It doesn't affect you?

06:30.549 --> 06:33.268
I don't have time.

06:33.302 --> 06:34.436
We don't have time.

06:34.470 --> 06:35.753
You want to protect David?

06:35.771 --> 06:38.690
We have to move fast,
and I need you to trust me.

06:38.724 --> 06:40.525
Trust you?

06:40.559 --> 06:43.028
You think a tough exterior
is going to cover the fact

06:43.062 --> 06:47.616
that you have no idea
how to handle Henry?

06:47.650 --> 06:49.451
I was married to him
for 11 years

06:49.485 --> 06:53.288
and his asset before that.

06:53.322 --> 06:55.073
He's better at this than you.

06:55.107 --> 06:56.941
Go home, Sana.

